wages => salarios
The main difference between salary and hourly wage is that salaries are a fixed upon payment agreed to by both the employer and employee. Wages, on the other hand, may vary depending on hours worked and performance

Fringe benefits are perks that employers give to their employers above and beyond any financial compensation

The prices of goods and services are driven by market forces

Market forces are the forces of supply and demand

These forces influence the priice and availability of goods and services in an economy

Market forces push up prices when supply declines and demand rises and drive them down when supply grows or demand contracts. 

